-- Madrid-Toledo Toll Highway Declares Bankruptcy, Cinco Reports
-- B y   A n g e l i n e   B e n o i t
-- 2012-05-11T05:43:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-11/madrid-toledo-toll-highway-declares-bankruptcy-cinco-reports.html
The highway between Madrid and
Toledo, which is managed by companies including Grupo Isolux
Corsan SA, Comsa SA, Azvi and  Banco Espiritu Santo SA (BES) , has
declared itself bankrupt at the Albacete court,  Cinco Dias 
reported, without saying how it obtained the information.  The AP-41 toll road has over 500 million euros ($646
million) of debt, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Angeline Benoit in Madrid at 
 abenoit4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at 
 cstirling1@bloomberg.net  